{"article_id":"ohSvu3cydcpQ1Nex","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Donald Trump is really , really excited about a Space Force -","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"his plan","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"to create an entirely new branch of the US military","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"dedicated to defending American satellites and more in space .","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"though it seemed for a while that the Pentagon might try to keep it from happening ,","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"it looks like Trump may actually get his wish -","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"that is , unless Congress turns him down .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"On Thursday , Vice President Mike Pence delivered a big speech","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"unveiling the Defense Department ' s official plan","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"to effectively create a Space Force in all but name .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Trump was ecstatic ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"tweeting","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"\" Space Force all the way ! \"","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"just minutes after Pence ' s speech ended .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"while the Pentagon can make certain moves","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"without Congress ' s approval ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"it ' s up to lawmakers to actually authorize the new military branch .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"\" Congress definitely gets a vote , \"","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Deborah Lee James , the last Air Force secretary and an open critic of the Space Force idea , told me .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Pence and Trump ' s argument","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"for creating a Space Force","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"boils down to this :","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"Enemies like China and Russia have , for example , tested technology","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to shoot down satellites ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"and the US wants to ensure","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"the US can adequately defend itself against growing threats .","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"\" What was once peaceful and uncontested is now crowded and adversarial , \"","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Pence said on Thursday at the Pentagon .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"\" It ' s not enough to merely have an American presence in space ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"we must have American dominance in space .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"And so we will . \"","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"The problem for Trump and Pence is that Congress hasn ' t shown the same desire for a Space Force -","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"in fact , they actually voted down a legislative proposal","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"to create it","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"last November .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"But the White House is now hopeful","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"they will receive congressional approval for the new military branch in the fiscal year 2020 defense budget .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"That ' s in part because of a seeming change of heart","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"- or at least , a capitulation -","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"from Secretary of Defense Jim Mattis .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"For much of last year , top Pentagon leaders railed against the idea of a Space Force .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"\" The Pentagon is complicated enough , \"","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Air Force Secretary Heather Wilson told reporters last summer .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"\" This will make it more complex ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"add more boxes to the organization chart. \"","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Mattis himself even came out against it .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"Now , though , Mattis is at least somewhat supportive publicly of the idea .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"Which means it ' s possible members of Congress may change their minds in Trump ' s favor .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"Expect Trump and Pence ' s greatest ally in Congress for a Space Force , Rep. Mike Rogers","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"( R-AL ) ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"to lead the way .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Rogers has said","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"that creating the new branch is necessary for US national security ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"particularly because other countries are catching up to America ' s power in space .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"\" Russia and China have become near peers , \"","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"Rogers told NPR in June 2017 .","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"\" They ' re close to surpassing us .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"What we ' re proposing would change that . \"","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"He ' s since led the legislative effort","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"to create the new military service .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Rogers tweeted his approval during Pence ' s remarks Thursday :","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"I am thrilled about the news today .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"We in the House have been warning for years about the threats to our space assets and the unacceptably slow pace","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"to develop more capable space systems .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"The report is a step in a multi-year process","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"that will help ensure a safer , stronger America","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"https : //t.co/12SwRkaz1c","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"- Mike Rogers","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"( @ RepMikeRogersAL )","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"August 9 , 2018","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"So what happens now ?","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"Well , in the short term , the Pentagon will do what it always does :","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"makes changes in an extremely bureaucratic , wonky , and boring way .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"Here ' s how the Pentagon will start creating a Space Force","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"The Pentagon released a report after Pence ' s speech","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"outlining four main things","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"it will do","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"to begin establishing a Space Force :","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Create a new Space Command ,","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"which will serve as the main Pentagon hub for all things","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"fighting in space","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"Establish the Space Operations Force ,","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"which will be made up of the military ' s elite troops","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"focusing on conflict in space","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"Create the Space Development Agency ,","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"which will help the Pentagon acquire weapons","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"to fight in space","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"Ensure","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"there are the requisite leaders and support staff","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"to manage the day-to-day operations of the Pentagon ' s operations in space","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"All of that boils down to the Defense Department making bureaucratic changes","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"to deal with space in the way","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Trump wants .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"The biggest loser in all of this will be the Air Force ,","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"which already takes the military lead","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"on defending American items in space","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"- like the satellites","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"that guide your GPS system -","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"with an agency","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"called the Air Force Space Command .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"It ' s unclear as of now , though ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"if that organization will go away or somehow fold under new Space Force .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"That ' s just one of the many , many questions","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"I and others have","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"about what a Space Force will actually look like .","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"There is one important thing","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"no one questions :","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"that space has become much more dangerous in recent years .","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"What was once the final frontier could soon become the front line of a future conflict .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"\" Space is no longer a peaceful domain , \"","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"James said in an interview in July 2017 .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"\" There is a real possibility","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"that a conflict on Earth could bleed into space . \"","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"There are two main reasons for that :","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"Russia and China .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"According to the Defense Intelligence Agency ,","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"Russia wants to gain more power in space","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"because it believes","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"gaining supremacy there will allow it to win future fights on this planet .","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"And in late 2015 , China created the Strategic Support Force ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"which is meant to streamline and improve its space , cyber , and electronic warfare missions .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"The two countries are causing problems with anti-satellite technology , too ,","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"noted Director of National Intelligence Dan Coats in a Senate Intelligence Committee hearing last May -","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"meaning they could mess with the satellites","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"that help the US military do its job .","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"The Pentagon is planning to open a space-war center","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"to counter their threats .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"Okay , but , like ... what sort of conflict is actually going on in space ?","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"What are we really talking about here ?","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"Basically , there is tons of military equipment in space , especially satellites .","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"This kind of equipment helps the US , Russia , and China","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"- and any tech-savvy force -","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"navigate terrain","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"and communicate with one another .","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"On top of that , assets in space help to track enemy fighters ,","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"take pictures for intelligence services ,","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"and even help control missiles .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"Without space support ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"it would be much harder to fight on Earth ;","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"that ' s why Russia and China are investing so heavily in it .","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"But Russia and China aren ' t space ' s only threats .","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"The area just outside Earth ' s orbit has seen an explosion of commercial satellites and other communications equipment since the 1960s ,","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"put there first by countries and , as of late , by commercial companies .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"That equipment is used","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"to help drivers reach their destination ,","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"help potential lovers swipe right","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"( or left )","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"on dating apps ,","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"or simply help people text a friend .","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"The chart below shows the huge growth in these satellites .","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"The blue line represents their total growth since around 1960 .","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"The internet , of course , adds a new complication to all the equipment","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"that countries are putting in space .","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"Most notably , equipment can potentially be hacked .","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"For instance , a team of hackers could jam a satellite","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"by messing with its signals","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"so it interrupts the satellite ' s normal activity ,","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"rendering it useless .","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"That could cause problems for all sorts of everyday activities , like credit card transactions and phone calls .","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"Then , of course , there ' s space debris","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"threatening all of that commercial and military space equipment ,","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"since it could knock into the expensive machines .","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"NASA estimates","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"that there are 20,000 pieces of debris larger than a softball","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"orbiting the Earth ,","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"about 500,000 pieces of debris the size of a marble or larger , and many millions of pieces","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"that are too small","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"to register .","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"All of this is why Trump , Rep. Rogers , and even former Defense Secretary Donald Rumsfeld believe","depth":8},{"id":171,"text":"the US needs a Space Force .","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"It would ensure the safety of space equipment","depth":9},{"id":173,"text":"by monitoring physical and cyberthreats against US communication and navigation assets .","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"It would be more of a defensive mission than an offensive one","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"- for now .","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"That doesn ' t mean actual troops in space yet .","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"But down the line , who knows ?","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"Essentially ,","depth":5},{"id":179,"text":"if the US military wants to protect life here on Earth ,","depth":6},{"id":180,"text":"it needs to safeguard US assets in space .","depth":6},{"id":181,"text":"But is a Space Force the way","depth":6},{"id":182,"text":"to do it ?","depth":6},{"id":183,"text":"The main issue is that Rogers and others","depth":11},{"id":184,"text":"- and perhaps Trump himself -","depth":11},{"id":185,"text":"believe","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"the Air Force isn ' t paying enough attention to space .","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"That makes sense to an extent ,","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"as the Air Force ' s main directive is to focus on flying planes here on Earth .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"Creating a new service would ensure","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"that there ' s a segment of the military","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"whose job is to focus on space 100 percent of the time .","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"That would allow the Space Force to counter Russia , China , and other threats","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"while giving space-focused staff more bureaucratic power inside the Pentagon .","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"But Sean O ' Keefe , a former NASA leader and Navy secretary , thinks","depth":10},{"id":195,"text":"creating a brand new branch of the military is not the right way to go .","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"\" This is a solution in search of a problem , \"","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"he told me in an interview last summer .","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"Basically , he thinks","depth":12},{"id":199,"text":"the Air Force is already doing a fine job","depth":14},{"id":200,"text":"protecting space","depth":14},{"id":201,"text":"- even if it does privilege earthbound pilots .","depth":13},{"id":202,"text":"Creating a Space Force would just add another layer of bureaucracy to an already massive organization :","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"the Pentagon .","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"James , the former Air Force secretary , agrees .","depth":10},{"id":205,"text":"She thinks","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"dealing with the current complaints about the Air Force and space","depth":14},{"id":207,"text":"- 1 ) that it ' s not well funded ,","depth":15},{"id":208,"text":"2 ) that acquisition takes too long ,","depth":16},{"id":209,"text":"and 3 ) that there is no one person","depth":17},{"id":210,"text":"to call about military space operations -","depth":17},{"id":211,"text":"makes more sense .","depth":13},{"id":212,"text":"The first complaint is already being mollified to an extent .","depth":13},{"id":213,"text":"The Air Force asked for a 20 percent increase in funds","depth":14},{"id":214,"text":"to focus on space in 2018 .","depth":14},{"id":215,"text":"As for the third complaint , James feels","depth":14},{"id":216,"text":"it ' s a common refrain","depth":16},{"id":217,"text":"heard at DOD","depth":16},{"id":218,"text":"that doesn ' t necessarily just apply to the Air Force and space .","depth":15},{"id":219,"text":"\" If you look at any warfare area in the Department of Defense ,","depth":15},{"id":220,"text":"there ' s no single bellybutton for anything , \"","depth":15},{"id":221,"text":"she told me .","depth":14},{"id":222,"text":"So clearly the Space Force has its detractors","depth":10},{"id":223,"text":"- including the current Air Force secretary .","depth":10},{"id":224,"text":"And of course , Congress has yet to officially mandate its creation .","depth":7},{"id":225,"text":"But with Trump ' s endorsement , the conversation has kicked into high gear once again .","depth":7},{"id":226,"text":"Time will tell","depth":2},{"id":227,"text":"if future US troops will be wearing space helmets .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":455,"left":453,"right":454,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":453,"left":356,"right":452,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":356,"left":299,"right":355,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":269,"right":298,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":242,"right":268,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":231,"right":241,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":231,"left":0,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":1,"right":229,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":234,"right":240,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":233,"right":7,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":4,"right":232,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":240,"left":236,"right":239,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":8,"right":235,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":11,"right":238,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":237,"right":14,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":268,"left":247,"right":267,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":245,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":244,"right":18,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":244,"left":15,"right":243,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":243,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":258,"right":266,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":258,"left":253,"right":257,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":249,"right":252,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":249,"left":248,"right":23,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":248,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":250,"right":251,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":250,"left":24,"right":25,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":26,"right":27,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":257,"left":254,"right":256,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":254,"left":28,"right":29,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":255,"right":32,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":30,"right":31,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":266,"left":261,"right":265,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":261,"left":33,"right":260,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":259,"right":36,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":259,"left":34,"right":35,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":262,"right":264,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":37,"right":38,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":264,"left":263,"right":41,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":263,"left":39,"right":40,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":276,"right":297,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":274,"right":275,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":273,"right":47,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":42,"right":272,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":272,"left":270,"right":271,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":270,"left":43,"right":44,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":271,"left":45,"right":46,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":275,"left":48,"right":49,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":297,"left":285,"right":296,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":278,"right":284,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":278,"left":277,"right":52,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":277,"left":50,"right":51,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":284,"left":279,"right":283,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":279,"left":53,"right":54,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":283,"left":55,"right":282,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":282,"left":281,"right":59,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":281,"left":280,"right":58,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":280,"left":56,"right":57,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":286,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":286,"left":60,"right":61,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":291,"right":294,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":291,"left":62,"right":290,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":290,"left":63,"right":289,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":289,"left":287,"right":288,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":287,"left":64,"right":65,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":288,"left":66,"right":67,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":294,"left":68,"right":293,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":293,"left":292,"right":71,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":292,"left":69,"right":70,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":355,"left":330,"right":354,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":330,"left":318,"right":329,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":318,"left":72,"right":317,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":317,"left":300,"right":316,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":300,"left":73,"right":74,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":316,"left":75,"right":315,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":315,"left":303,"right":314,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":76,"right":302,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":77,"right":301,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":78,"right":7